        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 6:35AM MST by NWS Flagstaff AZ</headline>
        <description>At 635 AM MST /735 AM MDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm over Antelope Island, or 5 miles north of Page, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Page, Trapeze Cove, Antelope Point Marina, Antelope Island, Page
Municipal Airport, Glen Canyon Dam, Antelope Canyon, LeChee,
Wahweap, Glen Canyon National Recreation Area, Golliard Park and
Lake Powell.

This includes the following slot canyons...
Lower Antelope Canyon and Labyrinth Canyon.

This includes the following highways...
U.S. Highway 89 between mile markers 548 and 554.
State Route 98 between mile markers 548 and 549.

This includes the following recreation areas and campgrounds...
Wahweap Campground and Page Lake Powell Campground.
</description>
